## The Protection

**21 USPTO provisional patent applications. 2,270 formal patent claims.** Filed by the Founder as a micro-entity. The filing protects cooperative infrastructure from extraction.

**228 Crown Jewels** across the portfolio. The Canister System's swappable-barrel architecture has no commercial equivalent. The three-currency system has mathematical solvency proofs. The Cost+20% margin lock is constitutionally embedded.

**Cooperative Defensive Patent Pledge (#2260) + SSPL license:** Every patent in the Liana Banyan portfolio is pledged defensively -- available to protect cooperative operators worldwide, not weaponizable against them. Eight Seeds (independent cooperative entities across multiple jurisdictions) can pick up a key and form an independent cooperative that inherits the full platform architecture and patent coverage from day one.

---

## The Founding Three Hundred

The Pay-It-Forward 300 is not a crowdfund. It is a founding circle.

Three hundred people -- chosen from existing relationships, people who do the actual work -- receive a patent allocation and a cooperative surplus allocation in exchange for agreeing to extend the same deal to anyone they ever bring into a cooperative arrangement of their own.

The deal, plainly stated: Our plan is to have the Founder hold an objective 20% of all patents filed -- that is the reservation kept. Of those, we are committing to hand out an objective 5% of all patents to the three hundred. The Founder is therefore left with an objective 15% of all patents. We intend this gift to be perpetual -- to survive the Founder.

Alongside that, each member of the three hundred receives a separate cooperative surplus allocation of Joules -- drawn from the Founder's own existing allocation. Joules buy things inside the cooperative. They do not cash out. Value stays inside the cooperative substrate and compounds there instead of leaking out.

The price: $5/year. Same as every other member.

**The recursion:** If you ever bring someone into a cooperative arrangement of your own, you give them the same deal. You keep 20%, you hand out 5%, you are left with 15%. And they, in turn, give the same deal to anyone they bring in. The deal propagates down the chain forever, with no decay at any layer.

This is not a network-marketing scheme. In extraction schemes, value flows from recruits up to recruiters, and each layer takes a smaller share. In this structure, value flows from founders out to recruits, and every layer gets the same magnitude of deal -- never less. Nobody is on the bottom. There is no bottom.

The reason it has to work this way is that cooperative IP has to compound or it dies. Same deal. All the way down. Forever.

---

## The Point

A little girl wanted to be an astronaut. Her mother listed everything it would take. Years of work. Enormous sacrifice. A path that most people would look at and say: impossible.

The girl looked at the list and saw three things.

Liana Banyan is the same list. Level the Field. Feed Your Neighbors. Employ the World. Build Businesses and Make Things. Power to the People. Belong Together.

That is just, like, six things.

The platform is built. The door is open. The kitchen is ready.

**Read the proofs at [lianabanyan.com/proofs](https://lianabanyan.com/proofs). Try it free at [lianabanyan.com](https://lianabanyan.com).**

